data.description: Welcome home to  2328 Reed Street. This enormous property is situated in the thriving Point Breeze neighborhood. An emerging, culturally diverse neighborhood supported by edgy coffee shops and dive pubs. Casual restaurants coexist with gastropubs run by chefs that serve craft beer. On Ellsworth Street, across from Keith Haring's artwork, the neighborhood comes alive during the warmer months with a spectacular pop-up beer garden and outdoor jazz performances. The home features four bedrooms, three and a half bathrooms, a gorgeously finished basement, and a balcony on the third floor. It recently had a complete renovation a few years ago and was freshly painted recently. The main bedroom has a walk-in closet, a good-sized bathroom, and a jacuzzi. The living and dining rooms are very roomy.  Across the street is the Wharton Square Playground, ideal for afternoon strolls, pet walks, etc. With public transportation available on 22nd St., Center City is a reasonably short distance away, as is University City. Set up an appointment right away to tour this homo.
